'''詹姆斯·大衛·凡斯'''（{{lang-en|James David Vance}}<ref name=GR>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32492072-summary---hillbilly-elegy|title=Summary - Hillbilly Elegy: By James David Vance - A Memoir of a Family and Culture in Crisis|work=GoodReads.com|accessdate=2017-05-10|archive-date=2019-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190306012032/https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32492072-summary---hillbilly-elegy|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="washPost6feb2017">{{cite web|last1=Heller|first1=Karen|title=‘Hillbilly Elegy’ made J.D. Vance the voice of the Rust Belt. But does he want that job?|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/hillbilly-elegy-made-jd-vance-the-voice-of-the-rust-belt-but-does-he-want-that-job/2017/02/06/fa6cd63c-e882-11e6-80c2-30e57e57e05d_story.html|website=[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]|access-date=2020-09-18|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125133721/https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/hillbilly-elegy-made-jd-vance-the-voice-of-the-rust-belt-but-does-he-want-that-job/2017/02/06/fa6cd63c-e882-11e6-80c2-30e57e57e05d_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，簡稱'''J·D·凡斯'''（{{lang-en|J. D. Vance}}），幼名'''詹姆斯·唐納·鮑曼'''（{{lang-en|James Donald Bowman}}）<ref name=EN>{{cite web|url=https://www.enotes.com/topics/hillbilly-elegy/characters|title=Hillbilly Elegy: A Memoir of a Family and Culture in Crisis|work=Enotes.com|accessdate=2017-05-10|archive-date=2018-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028041943/https://www.enotes.com/topics/hillbilly-elegy/characters|dead-url=no}}</ref>，{{bd|1984年|8月2日|||catIdx=Vance}}），為一名美國[[作家|作家]]兼[[風險投資|風險投資家]]。其成名作為回憶錄《[[絕望者之歌|絕望者之歌]]》（{{lang-en|Hillbilly Elegy}}），該書講述自己在[[阿巴拉契亞|阿巴拉契亞]]地區成長所接受的價值觀，以及該地區的一些社會問題。該書於2016年和2017年連續兩年蟬聯[[紐約時報暢銷書榜|紐約時報暢銷書榜]]中，並於2017年入圍[[戴頓文學和平獎|戴頓文學和平獎]]（{{lang-en|Dayton Literary Peace Prize}}）的決賽名單。<ref>Dayton Literary Peace Prize. http://www.daytonliterarypeaceprize.org/ {{Wayback|url=http://www.daytonliterarypeaceprize.org/ |date=20210509034131 }}</ref>該書亦於[[2016年美國選舉|2016年美國選舉]]期間備受美國媒體關注，成為外界了解美國白人工人階級的窗口。<ref name="NewYorker12sept2016">{{cite web|last1=Rothman|first1=Joshua|title=The Lives of Poor White People|url=http://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/the-lives-of-poor-white-people|website=[[紐約客|紐約客]]|accessdate=2017-03-06|archive-date=2021-01-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210102073802/https://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/the-lives-of-poor-white-people|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyTimes10aug2016">{{cite web|last1=SENIOR|first1=JENNIFER|title=Review: In ‘Hillbilly Elegy,’ a Tough Love Analysis of the Poor Who Back Trump|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/11/books/review-in-hillbilly-elegy-a-compassionate-analysis-of-the-poor-who-love-trump.html?_r=0|website=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]|accessdate=2017-03-06|archive-date=2021-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421040330/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/11/books/review-in-hillbilly-elegy-a-compassionate-analysis-of-the-poor-who-love-trump.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>

《絕望者之歌》除受到廣大的關注和正面回響外，亦受到了不少批評。一些阿巴拉契亞人稱，凡斯既不是正宗的希爾比利，也沒有資格代表白人工人階級。這些評論者認為，凡斯在書中將自己於曾童年時期多個暑期一起同住的希爾比利祖父母的經驗和身分認同，同自己的經驗和身分認同混為一談。<ref name="lexington21aug2016">{{cite web|last1=Kiser|first1=Brandon|title=Author too removed from culture he criticizes|url=http://www.kentucky.com/opinion/op-ed/article96779312.html|website=Lexington Herald-Leader|accessdate=2017-03-06|archive-date=2021-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210325191124/https://www.kentucky.com/opinion/op-ed/article96779312.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>亦有評論者認同凡斯對希爾比利文化的觀點。<ref name="lexington9sept2016">{{cite web|last1=Miles|first1=StefanieRose|title=Author J.D. Vance does have hillbilly cred — like it or not|url=http://www.kentucky.com/opinion/op-ed/article100925787.html|website=Lexington Herald Leader|accessdate=2017-03-06|archive-date=2020-12-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201227013911/https://www.kentucky.com/opinion/op-ed/article100925787.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

政治認同方面，凡斯表示儘管自己在社會議題上為保守派，但對當今[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]的許多政見持批評意見，尤其認為該黨的經濟政策因過於偏袒富人的利益而傷害到勞動階級的利益。

== 早年 ==
1984年8月，幼時全名為詹姆斯·唐納·鮑曼（{{lang-en|James Donald Bowman}}，當時隨父姓，後因父母離異改隨母姓）的詹姆斯·大衛·凡斯生於[[肯塔基州|肯塔基州]][[傑克遜_(肯塔基州)|傑克遜]]，生父母分別為唐納·鮑曼（{{lang-en|Donald Bowman}}）和貝弗·凡斯（{{lang-en|Bev Vance}}），兩人於凡斯幼年時期便離異，之後凡斯由母親的第三任丈夫收養。凡斯有一名為琳賽（{{lang-en|Lindsay}}）的姊姊，姊姊於母親19歲時出生。凡斯年幼時，母親因長年服用止痛藥而飽受藥癮困擾，之後甚至染上[[海洛因|海洛因]]，並多次離婚。<ref name=EN />由於父母未能提供自己和姊姊穩定的家庭環境，因此姊弟倆主要由祖父母撫養長大。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/dec/07/hillbilly-elegy-by-jd-vance-review|title=Hillbilly Elegy by JD Vance review – does this memoir really explain Trump’s victory?|date=2016-12-07|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-10-05|archive-date=2021-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420124518/https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/dec/07/hillbilly-elegy-by-jd-vance-review|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/the-lives-of-poor-white-people|title=The Lives of Poor White People|date=2016-09-12|work=The New Yorker|access-date=2020-10-05|archive-date=2021-01-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210102073802/https://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/the-lives-of-poor-white-people|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2016/08/17/490328484/hillbilly-elegy-recalls-a-childhood-where-poverty-was-the-family-tradition|title='Hillbilly Elegy' Recalls A Childhood Where Poverty Was 'The Family Tradition'|date=2016-08-17|publisher=NPR|access-date=2020-10-05|archive-date=2021-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210409210129/https://www.npr.org/2016/08/17/490328484/hillbilly-elegy-recalls-a-childhood-where-poverty-was-the-family-tradition|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 教育 ==
凡斯高中時期就讀位於自己家鄉的公立學校米德爾敦高中（{{lang-en|Middletown High School}}）。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.journal-news.com/news/middletown-native-vance-book-started-with-simple-question/wiUzBgVwzDhvk72sl8SnRP/|title=Middletown native J.D. Vance's book started with simple question|work=JournalNews.com|author=Michael D. Clark|date=2017-03-10|accessdate=2017-05-10|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202085301/https://www.journal-news.com/news/middletown-native-vance-book-started-with-simple-question/wiUzBgVwzDhvk72sl8SnRP/|dead-url=no}}</ref>高中畢業後，他進入[[美國海軍陸戰隊|美國海軍陸戰隊]]服役<ref name="militaryformermarinejdvance">{{cite web|title=Former Marine J.D. Vance's 'Hillbilly Elegy' Will Be Made into a Movie|url=http://www.military.com/off-duty/movies/2017/04/11/former-marine-jd-vance-hillbilly-elegy-will-be-made-movie.html|website=Military.com|accessdate=2017-07-27|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126050644/https://www.military.com/off-duty/movies/2017/04/11/former-marine-jd-vance-hillbilly-elegy-will-be-made-movie.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並曾被派遣到伊拉克，為美軍的公共事務部門服務。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ted.com/speakers/jd_vance |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-10-06 |archive-date=2021-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506212525/https://www.ted.com/speakers/jd_vance |dead-url=no }}</ref>退伍後，凡斯至[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]][[哥倫布_(俄亥俄州)|哥倫布]]的[[俄亥俄州立大學|俄亥俄州立大學]]就讀，並獲得了[[文學士|文學士]]學位。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://law.yale.edu/yls-today/news/jd-vance-speak-about-memoir-hillbilly-elegy-feb-2|title=J.D. Vance to Speak About Memoir Hillbilly Elegy Feb. 2|work=[[耶魯法學院|耶魯法學院]]|date=2017-01-27|accessdate=2017-05-10|archive-date=2020-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201014102417/https://law.yale.edu/yls-today/news/jd-vance-speak-about-memoir-hillbilly-elegy-feb-2|dead-url=no}}</ref>就讀大學期間，他曾為時任[[俄亥俄州參議院|俄亥俄州參議院]]的參議員[[鮑勃·舒勒|鮑勃·舒勒]]（{{lang-en|Bob Schuler}}）工作。<ref name="vancehillbilly181">{{cite book|last1=Vance|first1=J. D.|title=Hillbilly Elegy|date=2017|publisher=William Collins|location=London, U.K.|isbn=9780008220563|oclc=965479512|page=181|quote=I took a job at the Ohio Statehouse, working for a remarkably kind senator from the Cincinnati area named Bob Schuler. He was a good man, and I liked his politics, so when constituents called and complained, I tried to explain his positions.}}</ref>

自俄亥俄州立大學畢業後，凡斯前往[[耶魯法學院|耶魯法學院]]深造並獲得了[[法律博士|法律博士]]學位。在耶魯第一年的導師為[[蔡美兒|蔡美兒]]，蔡教授於日後凡斯決定撰寫自傳的時候給予不少鼓勵。<ref>{{cite magazine|title=How the 'Tiger Mom' Convinced the Author of Hillbilly Elegy to Write His Story|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2017/06/hillbilly-elegy-mentor/529443/|magazine=The Atlantic|date=2016-06-07|access-date=2020-10-06|archive-date=2021-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210413175048/https://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2017/06/hillbilly-elegy-mentor/529443/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 生涯 ==
自法學院畢業後，凡斯受聘於[[彼得·泰爾|彼得·泰爾]]的[[風險投資|風險投資]]公司秘銀資產管理有限公司（{{lang-en|Mithril Capital Management LLC}}），擔任主管職位。<ref name="washingtonpost1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-01-20/peter-thiel-s-mithril-capital-raises-850-million-vc-fund|title=Peter Thiel's Mithril Capital Raises $850 Million VC Fund|work=Bloomberg Technology|author=Sarah McBride|date=2017-01-20|accessdate=2017-05-10|archive-date=2021-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506175430/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-01-20/peter-thiel-s-mithril-capital-raises-850-million-vc-fund|dead-url=no}}</ref>2020年，凡斯為總部位於[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]][[辛辛那提|辛辛那提]]的納亞資本籌款9,300萬美元。<ref>{{cite news |last1=Loizos |first1=Connie |title=‘Hillbilly Elegy’ author J.D. Vance has raised $93 million for his own Midwestern venture fund |url=https://techcrunch.com/2020/01/09/hillbilly-elegy-author-j-d-vance-has-raised-93-million-for-his-own-midwestern-venture-fund/ |accessdate=2020-01-15 |work=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]] |date=2019-01-09 |archive-date=2021-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416062035/https://techcrunch.com/2020/01/09/hillbilly-elegy-author-j-d-vance-has-raised-93-million-for-his-own-midwestern-venture-fund/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2016年12月，凡斯表示自己打算移居至俄亥俄州，除計畫在當地創辦一家關注[[鏽帶|鏽帶]]地區藥物濫用問題的非營利組織，也有意參選公職。<ref name="washPost21dec2016">{{cite web|last1=Hohmann|first1=James|title=The Daily 202: Why the author of ‘Hillbilly Elegy’ is moving home to Ohio|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/powerpost/paloma/daily-202/2016/12/21/daily-202-why-the-author-of-hillbilly-elegy-is-moving-home-to-ohio/5859da6ee9b69b36fcfeaf48/|website=[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]|access-date=2020-10-07|archive-date=2021-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227164241/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/powerpost/paloma/daily-202/2016/12/21/daily-202-why-the-author-of-hillbilly-elegy-is-moving-home-to-ohio/5859da6ee9b69b36fcfeaf48/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="washPost6feb2017"/>該組織日後成立，被命名為「我們俄亥俄的復興」（{{lang-en|Our Ohio Renewal}}）。<ref>Our Ohio Renewal http://ourohiorenewal.com/ {{Wayback|url=http://ourohiorenewal.com/ |date=20201129065421 }}</ref>

2017年1月，凡斯成為[[有線電視新聞網|有線電視新聞網]]的評論員。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adweek.com/tvnewser/cnn-bolsters-its-roster-of-commentators-and-contributors/317459|title=CNN Strengthens its Roster of Commentators and Contributors|work=AdWeek.com|author=A. J. Katz|date=2017-01-17|accessdate=2017-04-27|archive-date=2021-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210408055800/https://www.adweek.com/tvnewser/cnn-bolsters-its-roster-of-commentators-and-contributors/317459/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年4月，[[朗·霍華|朗·霍華]]簽約同意執導《[[絕望者之歌|絕望者之歌]]》的[[絕望者之歌_(電影)|電影版]]。<ref>{{cite web|last1=Reed|first1=Ryan|title=Ron Howard to Direct, Produce 'Hillbilly Elegy' Movie|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/news/ron-howard-to-direct-produce-hillbilly-elegy-movie-w476022|website=[[滾石_(雜誌)|滾石]]|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-date=2017-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171122200535/http://www.rollingstone.com/movies/news/ron-howard-to-direct-produce-hillbilly-elegy-movie-w476022|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2018年1月，有報導指出凡斯有意代表共和黨參選[[聯邦參議員|聯邦參議員]]。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/henrygomez/jd-vance-is-now-seriously-considering-running-for-senate-in|title=J.D. Vance Is Now Seriously Considering Running For Senate In Ohio|last=Gomez|first=Henry|work=Buzzfeed|access-date=2018-01-11|language=en-US|archive-date=2018-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713190103/https://www.buzzfeed.com/henrygomez/jd-vance-is-now-seriously-considering-running-for-senate-in|dead-url=no}}</ref>

